# Tracking Configuration
# IMPORTANT: For email open/click tracking to work properly, these URLs MUST be:
# 1. Publicly accessible (not localhost in production)
# 2. Using HTTPS to avoid "Mixed Content" browser errors when emails are viewed on HTTPS sites
# 3. For local testing: Use a tunneling service like ngrok to get a public HTTPS URL
#    Example: ngrok http 3003 -> https://abc123.ngrok.io
#
# Mixed Content Error: If the email is viewed on an HTTPS site (e.g., web-based email clients),
# browsers will block/upgrade HTTP tracking pixel requests, causing tracking to fail.
# These tracking base urls are optional, if not provied the base url will be used by default
TRACKING_BASE_URL="https://your-public-domain.com"
TRACKING_CLICK_SUBDOMAIN="https://your-public-domain.com"
